      "span_text": "In one study, carried out on 143 HIV/HCV co-infected patients treated with PEG-INF/RBV who achieved ETR, all but 2 (45/47, 95.7%) relapses occurred before W12. [CITATION_1] Phylogenetic analysis suggested that HCV re-infection occurred in one patient, and the possibility that the second patient might have been exposed again to the same source that was the cause of her original infection could not be discounted.",
